        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I use {{actionStack}} helper in {{init()}} method (to create menu links and capture it's content).\nI also use {{ContextSwitch}} helper to make one action for ajax (json). Now, even when I try {{AjaxContext}}, when I call action with ajax call (?format=json) server returns 500 Internal Server error. When I removed actionStack from init() method it works well. Example code below.\n\n{code}\nclass EditorController extends Zend_Controller_Action\n{\n\tpublic function init()\n\t{\n\t\t$this->_helper->actionStack('menu', 'navigation');\n\n\t\t$contextSwitch = $this->_helper->getHelper('ContextSwitch');\n\t\t$contextSwitch->addActionContext('load', 'json')\n                      ->initContext();\n\t}\n\n    public function indexAction()\n    {\n    }\n\n    public function loadAction()\n    {\n    }\n{code}\n\nCall to \/editor\/load\/format\/json makes response unreachable.\n\nHowever i found that I can workaround it this way (part of {{init()}}:\n{code}\n        $actionContext = $contextSwitch->getActionContexts($this->_request->getActionName());\n        if (!in_array('json', $actionContext)) {\n        \t$this->_helper->actionStack('menu', 'navigation');\n        }\n{code}\n...but I think it should be automated, isn't it?"
        },
