        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24440",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What's happening here is that a context is activated -- which sets a new view\nscript suffix. As a result, any later actions on the ActionStack are now using\nthat altered view script suffix -- and likely do not have matching view scripts.\n\nThere are a few solutions. Probably the best, though, is simply to clear the\naction stack when a context is detected. You can do this with code like the\nfollowing:\n\n{code}\nif (null !== $this->_helper->contextSwitch->getCurrentContext()) {\n    $front = Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance();\n    if ($front->hasPlugin('Zend_Controller_Plugin_ActionStack')) {\n        $plugin = $front->getPlugin('Zend_Controller_Plugin_ActionStack');\n        $registry = $plugin->getRegistry();\n        unset($registry[$plugin->getRegistryKey()]);\n    }\n}\n{code}\n\nIf you swap the \"$this->_helper->contextSwitch\" part with \"Zend_Controller_Action_HelperBroker::getStaticHelper('ContextSwitch')\", you could even push that into a postDispatch() plugin.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-11T05:44:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-11T05:44:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26082",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zoki",
                        "name": "zoki",
                        "displayName": "Zoran Lazic",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That's not working as it should.\nYou shouldn't unset the whole key in the registry otherwise you'll get  \"Notice: Undefined index:  Zend_Controller_Plugin_ActionStack in .\/Zend_svn\/Zend\/Plugin\/ActionStack.php on line 136\"\n\ninstead\n  unset($registry[$plugin->getRegistryKey()]);\nit should be \n  $registry->{$plugin->getRegistryKey()} = array();\n\nMy ZF is: r12605",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zoki",
                        "name": "zoki",
                        "displayName": "Zoran Lazic",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-13T03:31:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-13T03:31:43.000+0000"
                },
